commit_message:
Always dump errors to console

When a job fails you would like to look in the logs for ERRORs but you can't
since there are so many bogus ERRORs masked by the whitelist. Now you will
see the non-whitelisted errors in the logs on failure.

Change-Id: I9ae041c218782b9b4431c8d89febdedd377bfbc9

commit_message:
Don't run volumes/disks checking in case
if node was provisioned

* add checking if node was provisioned
* make checking methods as protected
  instead of private, because they
  shouldn't be private from design point
  of view, it simplify unit testing

Closes-bug: #1262973
Change-Id: I036c16138c48054579eb1d8388d048ac7331c041

'}, {'account_id': 5292, 'date': '2013-12-19 23:08:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hi Sean,

In this specific case the v3 version does differ from the v1_1 version (the url prefix is different). 

There is another case where it really is exactly the same. I did think about just importing the v1_1 version but didn't because:

- mixing v1_1 and v3 imports in the code makes it harder to read/review code because there are specific cases where we want to import the v1_1 rather than v3 (in order to specialise it) and the imported code is only used in very specific ways. So its easier to pick up when something has accidentally remained unconverted. 

- when debugging its easier if you know you are always going to have a v3 object rather than a v1_1 sometimes. Eg something has definitely gone wrong if you start seeing v1_1 object when the v3 interface is meant to be used.

I don't feel hugely strongly about this - I realise there's a tradeoff here, so will change it to just import the v1_1 version if you still think that is better."}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2013-12-23 13:35:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Looks good to me (core reviewer); Approved

commit_message:
Adds keypairs support for the Nova V3 API

Adds support and tests for the keypairs extension for
the Nova V3 API. The V3 version of the keypair extension
has been made part of the core V3 API and as a result no longer
has the "os-" prefix in the url.

Differences between the V2 and V3 API are described here:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

Change-Id: Id4a77e1e4565f63ecdf7753d3c224975519fc07c

commit_message:
remove last errant file parse warning

provide a way to be able to instantiate the config object without
parsing a config file. This is expected to only be used for the
config file generator comparitor.

This means we finally don't generate warning messages on config
file parsing during our pep8 runs, and we do the right thing and
explode during tests if the config file doesn't exist in a real
way.

Change-Id: Ic4ae22814e2fdafc89a1997471283ccf8f3663bc

commit_message:
Factor out common image elements

Adds a DIB_COMMON_ELEMENTS env var that contains a list of elements
to be used in all image builds.  At this time that includes
pypi-openstack, pip-cache, and stackuser.

Change-Id: I74c39bc356f6064a5db4ddfdd86285672c4a656a

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-23 13:18:58.000000000', 'message': "Add class ModelsObjectComparatorMixin

Move class ModelsObjectComparatorMixin from nova.tests.db.test_db_api
to oslo-incubator, so we could reuse it in other projects.

This class have following methods:
- assertEqualObjects: check equal of the two dict, possible
exception of some keys.
- assertEqualListsOfObjects: check equal of the two lists. List's
object is dict.
- assertEqualListsOfPrimitivesAsSets: check equal of the two dict,
whose values are set.

Change-Id: Idbe607ea3fd42f35eafc8e38b7e75153998828a7
"}]
commit_message:
Add class ModelsObjectComparatorMixin

Move class ModelsObjectComparatorMixin from nova.tests.db.test_db_api
to oslo-incubator, so we could reuse it in other projects.

This class have following methods:
- assertEqualObjects: check equal of the two dict, possible
exception of some keys.
- assertEqualListsOfObjects: check equal of the two lists. List's
object is dict.
- assertEqualListsOfPrimitivesAsSets: check equal of the two dict,
whose values are set.

Change-Id: Idbe607ea3fd42f35eafc8e38b7e75153998828a7

commit_message:
SignalResponder store access/secret in resource data

We need to stop relying on the logic in heat_keystoneclient which
assumes there is only one keypair per user, as this assumption
may not remain true in future.

So instead, store the access/secret key in the DB as resource data,
which is probably better from a performance perspective anyway, and
will also allow SignalResponder subclasses to potentially override
the default credentials implementation more easily.

Change-Id: I7952181f30c94848acf358ab34cf17b6281d43ac
Partial-Bug: #1089261
blueprint: instance-users

commit_message:
chore: Bump version to icehouse-2 dev

This patch makes our version more specific in preparation for doing
interim project releases for each OpenStack milestone. The OS wiki
does not specify what to do about "development" versions, so I
decided to follow the standard Python convention.

Change-Id: Icae5b7abbb33969a60b3a517b9a016016180d0f5

Corrected grammar and messaging in translate.json

I updated several areas in translate.json to create messages that are more
clear, make them more generic for the community and corrected any grammatical
errors I saw.

commit_message:
rename old config object to TempestConfigPrivate

this attempts to make it clear to folks they should not be calling
this directly. The proxy is needed for lazy evaluation, so don't
call this.

Fix one issue where a config addition was landed before we got this
in tree.

Change-Id: I16eeee12aec4994c31a8bafdf12c7eddc98dff18

Get rid of fuel-ostf-tests

As this verification doesn't work
+ I didn't like this approach from start.

I am really happy to remove this sh** from Rally code.

Soon we will use tempest to verify that cloud work.

bp remove-fuel-ostf-tests

commit_message:
Add support for multiple encryption methods

We use only one encrypt() method but it returns the method to decrypt
the data. This way we can change the encryption mechanism but
always have a way to know how to decrypt whatever is stored.

Change-Id: I2315a33105a8766f69d02f0617af39a9dae19ddf
Partial-bug: #1251647

commit_message:
Add some negative tests for neutron floating_ip

These are the first negative tests for floating ip testing.
- Refactorization of floating_ips by creating base_floating_ips
- Create a negative tests file

Work in progress, do not merge.

Change-Id: I0c50f344fd5a0bc6347252c38ba39a49404de6bc
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Object-ify build_and_run_instance

The code for build_and_run_instance was put in place before the switch
to using Instance objects.  This updates the new boot process code to
use objects rather than dictionaries for instances.

bp remove-cast-to-schedule-run-instance

Change-Id: I47866536e924510d0d89d24336e0b690733c19e1

that are currently unused.

Roles are deleted for current release only

when release roles were updated.

Closes-Bug: 1263251

commit_message:
Fix check_networks task result

1. "id" renamed to "ids".
2. "ids" and "errors" are always lists.
3. "range_errors" removed.
4. "errors" values are subsets of NetworkGroup fields names.

Closes-Bug: #1263097

Change-Id: I30bb13c4613cf0b5a3f604ca350b2a594cbdf924

commit_message:
Add negative tests to lbaas api tests

lbaas api tests do not contain tests that check that if used fake
pool will not have be:
- created member/vip;
- accosiated health_monitor.
Also it is not checked that pool can not be deleted if there is a vip
created from it.

Closes-bug: #1262113

Change-Id: Iec0e47dddeb4a31baa9e6fe80369eced9c487ede

commit_message:
Disable heat for RHOS, backport swift ring builder for RHOS 3.0

Heat manifests still lack qpid support, so it needs
to be disabled during deployment.
Swift ring builder output changed for Havana, but a backport
is needed for RHOS 3.0.
Changes marked as FIXME

Change-Id: I75ec9c861119f975fa37cac875c5203272443ed8
Closes-Bug: #1263359
Related-Bug: #1263331

Allow plugin driver to create/delete l2 port on vip creation/deletion.
Plugin driver may have better knowledge about how to wire vip into the
tenant network. Also there is possible to share l2 ports for multiple vips.

Noop driver and haproxy plugin drivers are updated with common method
that creates l2 port.
That is done via SingleVipDriver that implements that common method.

fixes bug 1207986

commit_message:
Delegate port creation to the plugin driver

Allow plugin driver to create/delete l2 port on vip creation/deletion.
Plugin driver may have better knowledge about how to wire vip into the
tenant network. Also it is possible to share l2 ports for multiple vips.

Haproxy and Radware plugin drivers are updated with common method
that creates l2 port. Nicira service plugin was also fixed with corresponding
code.

Also, due to async and multithreading nature of radware driver, corresponding
tests were changed to manual vip deletion.

Closes-Bug: #1207986

Change-Id: I91d688912881ea12332cc592004efb8e1d4a09a8

Mark, we aren't talking about production here. SQLite 3 is used by default in Debian, because it requires absolutely no configuration at all from the user, so it can be setup in a completely automated way. Please do not just put a -2 like that without thinking about the consequences, which is a failed piuparts test.

If you don't want to do the work, I understand, though please don't prevent others from doing it."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2013-10-20 15:06:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I am ok with supporting sqlite.
From what Thomas wrote it seems that for debian supporting sqlite is a requirement.

However, since my level of knowledge about sqlalchemy + sqlite is pretty much close to absolute zero, I find a little bit difficult to understand details such as why one should set server_default instead of default, or stringify constants. This is why, in another bug report for sqlite migration issues, I asked for a blueprint.

I did so not because I want to be pedant (although I am pedant) but just because I'd like to have somebody who fixes all migrations, and also provides some guidelines in developer documentation about how to write migrations which are sqlite-compatible."}, {'account_id': 6476, 'date': '2013-10-20 16:34:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hi,
From what I can see, drop_column() isn't supported in SQLA with SQLite, as well as create_unique_constraint(). For both functions, it is needed to create a temporary table, then copy the content of the old table in it, then move over. This is described here:
http://sqlite.org/faq.html#q11

Alembic author perfectly knows this, but doesn't wish to implement it himself. However, it seems he would be ok to receive patches for it:
https://bitbucket.org/zzzeek/alembic/issue/21/column-renames-not-supported-on-sqlite

As you can see, it doesn't seem completely overkill to add such support in Alembic. Yes, it's going to be slow, though that's not what we should care about with SQLite (we only care it exists and can help with testing, in particular for me, piuparts tests, which are great to check the upgrade from one version of OpenStack to the next).

I think the best thing we could do for the future, would be to implement the missing functionality in Alembic. Though in the mean while, op.create_unique_constraint() and op.drop_column() shouldn't be used at all, since they seem not supported (I'm still investigating create_unique_constraint())."}, {'account_id': 6476, 'date': '2013-10-22 09:28:39.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-10-22 10:27:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Doesn't seem to work

commit_message:
Fix alembic migration

This patch fixes migration 128e042a2b68_ext_gw_mode.py,
63afba73813_ovs_tunnelendpoints_id_unique.py and
f9263d6df56_remove_dhcp_lease.py with SQLite 3. For these
last 2, it replaces create_unique_constraint() and
drop_column() by the corresponding SQL statements using
a temporary table (which is the only way with SQLite 3).

Closes-Bug: #1241577

Change-Id: I6c81c30302f98f7d3ca733f280ec1ae7dd802f55

commit_message:
Fix case error in qpid exchange type "direct"

Most places correctly have "direct", but one place has "Direct"
instead, which is incorrect.

Fixes bug #1211338

(cherry picked from commit bec54ac5fb6a190c98079537f63d2f0e17584d21)

Change-Id: I2516317ff7f6ff18ee0a99a60d0c058ed309d4da

lifeless - I think the docs describe ambiguity, but the code is unambiguous. If you specify something in 5th field, it is always treated as a ref. To specify the cleanup option, you have to put it in th 6th field and include a ref.

Ooh ... funky, you can do:

 ironic git /usr/local/ironic git://git.openstack.org/openstack/ironic.git  cleanup

i.e. double space between 4th and 6th fields to indicate the 5th field is empty and should default to master. Hmm.

Maybe we want to greedy match for whitespace between fields e.g.

commit_message:
Add a cleanup option to source-repositories

This allows element writers to express that the destination directory
should be removed during the cleanup phase before finalising the image.

The use case for this is source trees that are used to install code
elsewhere, for example pulling down OpenStack just to pip install from the
git tree into a virtualenv. The tree does not need to stay in the image.

Removing these trees will make the images smaller which should improve
build/upload/transfer times.

Change-Id: I9a599c8b713a865579873f2cf5b3667b5d4b34b1

commit_message:
Specify targets in the first line of template file

The format of the first line to specify targets:

... TARGETS=path1,path2,...

And the target path can be variables, which is determined in json when
applying configuration.

If TARGETS are not specified, original output file will be used.

Change-Id: I57cfddf5f26a7efd651ea81a4d34cb7ea7707730
Closes-Bug: #1258351

commit_message:
Use DictOpt for mapping options

oslo.config supports dictionary options from version 1.2.0a1.
Currently the mapping options in neutron are using ListOpts which
does not well match their usage. Using DictOpt would be more intuitive.

Fixes bug #1237162

Change-Id: I7d9009db31cf14e45e0d480c5ba5dd716f005290

commit_message:
Install Guide: Clarify database node setup

Some people were not aware that they needed to install MySQL packages
on nodes. This patch rearranges the code so that we have separate
sections for controller and node and thus readers should easily
spot what needs to be done.

Change-Id: I104b949466b426e102d55bcb3c4a9cb72a0a6af9
Closes-Bug: #1250600
backport: havana

I'm also reluctant to suggest unofficial binaries. I would suggest some text like this:

The simplest way to install the Python clients is to use the "pip" Python package manager. Unfortunately, the official Python Windows installer does not install "pip", or the "setuptools" package that pip depends on. 

If you already have Python installed on your system, you have several options: 

* You can manually install setuptools and then pip. (See the setuptools install documentation <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools#windows> and pip install documentation <http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/installing.html> 
* You can install pip using a tool called "pip-win" <https://sites.google.com/site/pydatalog/python/pip-for-windows>.
 * You can install setuptools and pip using unofficial windows binaries mainatained by Christophe Gohlke <http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/>

If you don't already have Python installed on your system, you can install an unofficial Python distribution that includes pip, such as: 

 * ActivePython Community edition <http://www.activestate.com/activepython/downloads> (check the PyPM option in the installer to ensure that pip is installed)
 * Use Chocolately NuGet <http://chocolatey.org/> to install Python (`cinst python`) and then install pip (`cinst pip`)'}, {'account_id': 7923, 'date': '2013-12-08 19:35:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Added step to make sure 'root_helper' key references 'neutron'

In the current Neutron Havana packages for RHEL-style distributions,
the default 'root_helper' key in neutron.conf references 'quantum'
instead of 'neutron'. This issue should get fixed upstream, but in
the meantime I added a step to make sure this key references
'neutron'.

Change-Id: I25f9faaba1067040829633aff990d238f5bf4ced
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1258309

commit_message:
Correct auth configuration for identity in Havana.

In Havana, there are some changes for auth configuration. Auth methods
configuration should include external authentication method if it is
configured in keystone.conf explicitly.

Change-Id: I0288834eb0964f0fffe0b2e674016c51cddd2386

commit_message:
Updates tox.ini to use new features

Reasons:
 - tox update v1.6

Changes:
 - tox 1.6 allows us to skip the sdist step, which is slow.
 - It also allows us to override the install line. In this case, it's
   important as it allows us to stop getting pre-release software we
   weren't asking for.

Original patch by Monty Taylor, talked about here:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-September/015495.html

Change-Id: Idbf8e08383232ae0af5b245c1abe91a7f852bfcf

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-20 16:21:19.000000000', 'message': 'disable SIGHUP restart behavior

SIGHUP should only be a restart action for a daemonized processs,
when used on a console process SIGHUP should == SIGTERM. However
there is no detection about whether this service is actually
daemonized.

This change makes it so that SIGHUP == SIGTERM until someone
implements the detection. Until this is merged (and synced with
nova) unstack.sh is broken, and not really fixable on the devstack
side. This will impact future upgrade testing.

Change-Id: I2a73d3872a302fcfac1a6ee844a44faa9569b3dd
Partial-Bug: #1263122
'}, {'created': '2013-12-20 17:48:10.000000000', 'message': 'disable SIGHUP restart behavior in foreground

SIGHUP should only be a restart action for a daemonized processs,
when used on a console process SIGHUP should == SIGTERM. Add
detection for whether this service is actually daemonized.

Change-Id: I2a73d3872a302fcfac1a6ee844a44faa9569b3dd
Fixes-Bug: #1263122
'}, {'created': '2013-12-20 17:59:29.000000000', 'message': 'disable SIGHUP restart behavior in foreground

SIGHUP should only be a restart action for a daemonized processs,
when used on a console process SIGHUP should == SIGTERM. Add
detection for whether this service is actually daemonized.

Change-Id: I2a73d3872a302fcfac1a6ee844a44faa9569b3dd
Fixes-Bug: #1263122
'}]
commit_message:
disable SIGHUP restart behavior in foreground

SIGHUP should only be a restart action for a daemonized processs,
when used on a console process SIGHUP should == SIGTERM. Add
detection for whether this service is actually daemonized.

Change-Id: I2a73d3872a302fcfac1a6ee844a44faa9569b3dd
Fixes-Bug: #1263122

commit_message:
Indicate pseudo-folders in containers panel

The column that shows size of Objects is empty for pseudo folders.
We now indicate that this is a pseudo-folder.
Column does not have a column header so should not be confusing.
Also, show the size if the object is of size 0, (thanks Tihomir)

Closes-Bug: #1260859
Change-Id: I1ac233f5b964befa3d4f36c9a3d309383d691d28

Passing nodes more consistently

At some functions where only the node uuid is required the whole node
object is passed.

commit_message:
Fix QoS information in initialize_connection() result

Currently the entire QoS information (if any) is included in the result of
initialize_connection() even if the consumer of the QoS is 'back-end'. Also
the format for QoS specs also is changed so that front-end (Nova) can
parse correctly. Add unit test to cover initialize_connection().

Closes-bug: 1259957

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ibc5e92cc1ddf6404e5b234ef524698feae282eec

commit_message:
Document security group when using ML2 plugin

Since the ML2 plugin can concurrently support different L2 agents (or
other mechanisms) with different configurations, Neutron developpers
recommend setting firewall_driver flag in ml2 configuration.

Change-Id: I7f97128a955ded99400e25a5ef9a990260df3bf7
Closes-bug: #1262678
backport: havana
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
(cherry picked from commit 4c5d9ba37bb2cebedb05aabab3452a5e0005f985)

commit_message:
Implement matchmaker for ZeroMQ

ZeroMQ in devstack is configured to use redis, which is not the reccomended
configuration, and is not working. This patch changes the matchmaker to ring,
and creates all topics with a default of the local machine's hostname.

This is dependent upon I8514f178 in cinder

Change-Id: I3f62f7a9d6c7cd576abadefe43d61e952834d1b3
Partial-Bug: #1185690

commit_message:
Pin Sphinx to <1.2

1.2 was just released and has a bug that causes builds to fail with
the error:

  error: 'source_dir' must be a directory name (got `...doc/source`)

See: http://bugs.python.org/issue19570
and: https://bitbucket.org/birkenfeld/sphinx/pull-request/193/builddoc-shouldnt-fail-on-unicode-paths/diff

Change-Id: I0487b4eca8f2755b882689289e3cdf429729b1fb

commit_message:
Make live migration RPC tasks timeout configurable

Add an option live_migration_rpc_timeout for live migration pre/post methods.
Some of these cost a long time to return, so rpc_response_time isn't suit for
those RPC methods. For instance, pre_live_migration on destination node take
a long time if the base image of the instance to be moved is not yet cached
and large. The default RPC timeout of 60s is insufficient for this.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I2accfdda59f8aa74a95910d2be081ad94d5e4490
Closes-Bug: 1243601

commit_message:
RFC: Call create_test_server in setUp() method

If a server creation fails with create_test_server() in setUpClass,
the server would not be removed because tearDownclass is not called.
As the result, many BuildError servers are created and "Quota exceeded"
happens if server creations continue to fail.

This patch moves create_test_server call to each setUp() method for
deleting BuildError servers in tearDownClass.

NOTE:
 This patch is imcomplete, we need to fix the other many test files.
 There is alternative patch(I55bb386bbea550de11cc7a81c5d056680057523b).
 I'd like to know which way is best for fixing this problem.

Change-Id: I6f86bb63f3fafd5561f88785567aa7ec45d36d22
Related-Bug: #1257641

commit_message:
Replace dict.iteritems() with six.iteritems()

dict.iteritems() was replaced with dict.items() in Python 3. Use the
six.iteritems() function to get code compatible with Python 2 and Python 3.

Change-Id: I0c8ecc3ae540ffaf4c6b159e09ca16ccf365973d

commit_message:
Encode response from FakeHTTPClient

While working on [1], found that python 3.3 gate is failing [2].

In python 3.3 requests library expects response to be encoded. So encode
the same if it is not already.

Also add test for FakeHTTPClient.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/58067
[2] http://logs.openstack.org/67/58067/4/check/gate-python-solumclient-python33/15dc135/console.html.gz

Part of blueprint make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: I9af04e52bfa38f5c943dbc4929abb5e3161ef9b4

commit_message:
Fix cinder test cases when cinder extensions are in use

When cinder extension like extended_snapshot_attributes or volume_mig_status_attribute
are used this laters add extra attributes to response of queries 'show' and 'detail' but
not 'list', which mean the return response from 'show' and 'list' will not be identical,
so we should only compare result from 'list' and 'show' of specific attribute e.g.
id, display_name ... .

Closes-Bug: #1245377
Change-Id: I52fd9cf7cb2e67c04f575bfeb00e66660e00947d

commit_message:
Reduce the severity of dhcp related log traces

Due to timing issues, when the agent synchronizes
with the server wrt the representation of server's
and agent's networks, networks may have already
been deleted from the db. In such circumstances,
it is more appropriate to emit warnings rather than
full-blown exceptions as the agent handles these
circumstances just fine.

Close-bug: 1251874

(cherry picked from commit f1b9ac5a542a3125d757094fccda80c80c6dd420)

Conflicts:

        neutron/agent/dhcp_agent.py

Change-Id: I4b118b6087c7f42226f0d4265d2176c028d99f22

[{'created': '2013-12-21 16:17:12.000000000', 'message': "Work around broken cloud-init ephemeral disk code

Cloud-init cannot handle ephemeral disks like '/dev/sda1'. This prevents
the nova baremetal default from working properly. So if the ephemeral
disk isn't already mounted, we mount it just before we need it.

Closes-Bug: #1263294

commit_message:
Work around broken cloud-init ephemeral disk code

Cloud-init cannot handle ephemeral disks like '/dev/sda1'. This prevents
the nova baremetal default from working properly. So if the ephemeral
disk isn't already mounted, we mount it just before we need it.

Change-Id: Ide0e5ed3eff91755aac7d8f1e9c43f723f7bf3d5
Closes-Bug: #1263294

commit_message:
Fix AttributeError on BadRequest in scenario tests

Fixing the following incorrectly raised exception:

_StringException: Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "tempest/scenario/manager.py", line 251, in tearDownClass
    if e.__class__.__name__ == 'NotFound' or e.status_code == 404:
AttributeError: 'BadRequest' object has no attribute 'status_code'

Change-Id: I3ee006720328c0a5aabbc7766f997a032dfa8230

commit_message:
Support MTU configuration for LibvirtHybridOVSBridgeDriver

Allow other MTU configuration for the tap device and the veth pair
then MTU 1500 when LibvirtHybridOVSBridgeDriver is used.

unittest: Add testcases for device MTU config

Co-Authored-By: Thomas Bechtold <t.bechtold@telekom.de>
Closes-Bug: #1260697
Change-Id: I964eb263e514866ffd15a50005296ee85135a9f5

commit_message:
Catch NotImplementedError for vnc in the api

When a driver doesn't provide VNC consoles, it will raise
NotImplementedError back up to the API.  Catch this and return a 501.

Change-Id: I6b38be2b3b46dbaecfdb42ea9a139e3b691de193

commit_message:
Revert recent change to ComputeNode

This reverts the object-related parts of 4c21f4a. The problems with
it are:

- It didn't bump the object version
- It introduced a JSON blob string attribute to the object,
  which is unversioned structured data, which can't be
  checked or guaranteed during upgrades.

The first one, of course, breaks live upgrade because an older
node receives fields it doesn't know about, but should based on
the version.

Offending change I75e339c2a2827875078c937e57c37e85d3ad1852

commit_message:
extra_dhcp_opt add checks for empty strings

When passing extra-dhcp-opt into the port-create where an empty string
is provided as opt_value='   ', the create and update routine will load the
empty string into the DB. The result when written to the opts file is:
"tag:ece4c8aa-15c9-4f6b-8c42-7d4e285734bf,option:server-ip-address", which
when read by dnsmasq has been tested to cause dnsmasq to segment fault.

Change-Id: I31de4a3d27092bb219d20221c5ef5a6b22e050dc
Closes-Bug: #1257467

commit_message:
XenAPI: Update DomU to Ubuntu Saucy

Driven by a race condition in LVM being hit in the tempest
tests.  This is a locking race between a file lock and a
semaphore which is fixed in 2.02.96-5.

Change-Id: I8a8c215c90a0602288292ffd06b7694d2db6219e

HEAT_FETCHED_TEST_IMAGE may not be defined in some cases.

Some scripts that source stackrc use set -u, which will error
when unknown variables are accessed

'}, {'created': '2013-12-20 11:23:35.000000000', 'message': 'Fix the option of a2ensite command

devstack fails with trema when  execute
"sudo a2ensite sliceable_switch" command, without ".conf" filename extension
with Apache2.4, Apache2.22. With Apache 2.2, it successes.
Because in the versions which newer than version 2.2,
file checking of a2ensite command is more severe.
So, a2ensite command forbid "sliceable_switch" without "/conf".

Added ".conf" filename extension.

Change-Id: I29a03cb59ee493345b7df0f1a9189eb3516c86e2
Closes-Bug: #1263017
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the option of a2ensite command

devstack fails with trema when  execute
"sudo a2ensite sliceable_switch" command, without ".conf" filename extension
with Apache2.4, Apache2.22. With Apache 2.2, it successes.
Because in the versions which newer than version 2.2,
file checking of a2ensite command is more severe.
So, a2ensite command forbid "sliceable_switch" without "/conf".

Added ".conf" filename extension.

Change-Id: I29a03cb59ee493345b7df0f1a9189eb3516c86e2
Closes-Bug: #1263017

commit_message:
Explicily enable the stores used by devstack

Devstack currently relies on the default value of the `known_stores`
configuration option. This patch enables explicitly the default stores
used by devstack.

The real fix for the issue below will land in Glance. However, since the
default stores will be FS and HTTP we need devstack to enable Swift's as
well, which is required in the gates, hence this patch.

Partially-fixes: #1255556
Change-Id: Id9aab356b36b2150312324a0349d120bbbbd4e63

[{'created': '2013-12-20 03:03:19.000000000', 'message': 'config: get_meta_section() misunderstands the beginning of metasection

For example, the line, "if [[ -n $no_proxy ]]; then" is misparsed
as the beginning of metasection because get_meta_section() misses
escaping of "|" unlike get_meta_section_files().
This patch adds necessary escape as "|" -> "\|".

Change-Id: Ic14b2ac167037c4f5db89492f0e8a4c5b13c7b6d
Closes-Bug: #1262960
'}]
commit_message:
config: get_meta_section() misunderstands the beginning of metasection

For example, the line, "if [[ -n $no_proxy ]]; then" is misparsed
as the beginning of metasection because get_meta_section() misses
escaping of "|" unlike get_meta_section_files().
This patch adds necessary escape as "|" -> "\|".

Change-Id: Ic14b2ac167037c4f5db89492f0e8a4c5b13c7b6d
Closes-Bug: #1262960

commit_message:
Allow specifying CM alarm evaluation interval

The patch allows users to configure Ceilometer alarm evaluation interval.
We can add CEILOMETER_ALARM_EVALUATION_INTERVAL=10 in localrc to evaluate
alarms every 10 seconds instead of the default 60 seconds.

Change-Id: Ie2f2dc93b5915845b6dcbf8ac9d15ca0fe800c5a

My understanding of the least common denominator for supported browsers is the max cookie size per domain is 4093 bytes (i.e., sum of the size of all cookies for a domain). There is at least one user preferences cookie that can be set that will use some of the available 4093 bytes.  Certainly if you are over 4096 bytes in the one cookie you are over the limit, but there is some false negative possibility on this check.

Logging error if cookie size is > 4KB

When session storage is configured to use signed cookies, logging error when
cookie size is > 4KB.

commit_message:
Fix help of some optional arguments

Some positional arguments are optional but the help indicate
they are mendatory and can be confuse for an user.

  swift delete <container> [object]
  swift post <container> [object]

commit_message:
Add missing __contains__() and get() methods to QuotaUsage

The QuotaUsage class was missing __contains__() and get() methods which was
causing unexpected behaviour, e.g:

    >>> usages = quotas.tenant_quota_usages(request)
    >>> 'ram' in usages
    False
    >>> usages.get('ram')
    None

Change-Id: Ib0b1ad69c4bf4effd7c10827d23bcc713bdc5ed6

commit_message:
Set Keypair create button disabled when quota exceeded

We should disable create button when quota exceeded like creating instances.

Change-Id: I9cd044c195ccc1160f7d5cb0ee24fc346669d4d7
Fixes: bug #1250825

commit_message:
Add check for BlockDeviceMappingV2 nova extension

Booting instance from image (creates a volume) option is using
the new BDM format when submitting the create server request to
Nova. Adding a check for Nova extensions if it is supported
before displaying the option.

Closes-bug: #1223875

In the original fix API call is not wrapped with try/except
and it was fixed in bug 1262223 in master. The fix is also
cherry-picked from commit a10436e6a376fb2c3478796e7ad728eb0e1f0ba3.

Related-bug: #1262223

Change-Id: Ie0b2b5d574babc910e2dac7ce9e3ab6603382ffb
(cherry picked from commit a10436e6a376fb2c3478796e7ad728eb0e1f0ba3)

commit_message:
port related volumes tests into nova v3 part2

there is no cinder proxy in nova v3 api. So we just use cinder
directly. And some tests are duplication with the tests in cinder
testing, just remove them, add merge the remain tests under the
server tests directory.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: I41f0ac3292b84e2a905e5bbfb6e0fcdddf93b50b

commit_message:
Redundant validation for rebuild

Remove the redundant validation for rebuild. In fact that this extension
is registered as WSGI action implies that the body must contain a key with
the same name as action

Change-Id: I101ca74a015d0615736fba2080c3bb3e4cbdc96d
Closes-bug: #1254982

Hi Wen Xiang, from general programming perspective, it would be better to have the code explicitly declare each parameter and value, rather than relying upon any 'default' value or 'default' behavior. The 'default' behavior is not controlled by your code, so that potentially your code may be impacted by others.
For this refactoring, I believe this default behavior, 'starting from 0', will never change. So your code change is harmless. However, I also feel it will not benefit anyone. Furthermore, if we accept this change, will code reviewers also need to keep in mind to remind others not to write (0, 10) anymore? I think that is useless."}, {'account_id': 6282, 'date': '2013-12-13 08:36:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

1. range(10) => Very clear, loop 10 time
2. range(0, 10) => Of course, we also know 10 times, but not so graceful.
3. To make code clearer and graceful, developer should follow range(10). we use python, not perl. :)'}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-12-21 06:03:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned

Remove start index 0 in range()

commit_message:
Replace uuidutils.generate_uuid() with str(uuid.uuid4())

Oslo is deprecating/removing uuidutils during the icehouse cycle.
Consequently we need to remove all references to uuidutils, and
replace them with the corresponding function from trove.utils.

Closes-bug: 1253497

Change-Id: I7f877238fdad6a6160c927bee0bd8e4f8d638117

commit_message:
Modular L2 TypeDriver refact (ovs-agent)

Deprecate the segmentation_id/physical_network inside segment, only keep
network_type as required. And type driver can extend segment with
arbitrary data, also take charge of storing the data. The service pass
the entire segment to the agent instead of 3 separate arguments.

This is ovs agent patch

Change-Id: I9b76a7f79607a64570a05d44a1bfea591d78148c
Implements: blueprint ml2-typedriver-extra-port-info

'}, {'account_id': 105, 'date': '2013-07-30 17:14:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

So, rather than implementing this "extra port info" BP for ML2, which so far is apparently only needed to distinguish between VXLAN with and without multicast, Bob and I talked about another approach. We thought of making the physical_network component of the 3-tuple being composed of "physical network | multicast group", with both being optional. If we do that, we don't need this BP. It's an idea we thought we'd throw out there.

Another alternative is to use Aaron Rosen's BP here [1], which allows for multiple provider networks. This provides a dictionary for each port, and we could have separate keys for physical_network and multicast_group.

We should discuss this at the ML2 meeting tomorrow at 1400UTC Wednesday.

[1] https://blueprints.launchpad.net/neutron/+spec/map-networks-to-multiple-provider-networks'}, {'account_id': 7170, 'date': '2013-07-31 10:54:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

IMO, the 3-tuple is limiting the power of type drivers, it is impossible for every type driver store all infomation in the tuple. Some method should be introduced to store arbitrary data in the type driver, and the method may replace the 3-tuple.

commit_message:
Modular L2 TypeDriver refact (service)

Deprecate the segmentation_id/physical_network inside segment, only keep
network_type as required. And type driver can extend segment with
arbitrary data, also take charge of storing the data. The service pass
the entire segment to the agent instead of 3 separate arguments.

Now agent changes are in separate patches

Change-Id: Idf1b717059d4da7c2d6ca83f2217064bc3234447
Implements: blueprint ml2-typedriver-extra-port-info

[{'account_id': 9276, 'date': '2013-11-05 16:54:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: (3 inline comments)

Some changes needed before this is ready I think, Divyesh.'}, {'account_id': 901, 'date': '2013-11-05 21:45:32.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 9276, 'date': '2013-11-06 10:10:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)

Just one thing, Divyesh.  A change that needs to be submitted under another ticket crept in here.'}, {'account_id': 901, 'date': '2013-11-14 19:33:44.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2013-11-18 04:18:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

You have to think client side here. Take the situation where you are developing an application that is doing some orchestartion work and needs to talk to keystone. We can't have the library dictating config file options and locations onto the program that is going to use it. The only place OSLO.config is used in keystoneclient is in middleware as this is going to be run from a server and we are simply tryin to provide consistency in the options. 

I also don't think we ever want to simply replace the various crud managers. For the same reasons as mentioned in your blueprint this is going to require code syncs in one direction or the other.

Instead we are going to need a way of allowing an extension to add additional information to manager responses and add new managers. How we go about this is a very interesting problem."}, {'account_id': 2218, 'date': '2013-11-20 15:47:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Do not merge

(2 inline comments)

Hate to kill your enthusiasm here, but this is headed in the wrong direction.

I'm not certain that "plugins" is the right approach for the python-keystoneclient library in general, but even if it is, you are writing a custom mechanism that should, instead, reue one of the existing plugin approaches.

We need a client factory that can read an existing set of config options.

The keystoneclient really should just reflect "core" keystone behavior.  Additional behavior, from extensions or other locations, should either be explicitly added to the library, or done as out of tree code.  This code can consume the keystoneclient code, but does not need to be called from it.


Note that there is a common CLI effort, and your plugin approach is more relevant there than in in KC.  KC is moving toward a pure library, with CLI functiojnality to be deprecated in favor of the common CLI over time.'}, {'account_id': 901, 'date': '2013-11-20 18:43:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@ayoung: I am quite puzzled by your review comments:

1. The changes being proposed absolutely guarantee "core" keystone behavior and do not require any changes from the consumers of the client. _This was a core requirement and as such the proposed code changes fulfill it quite successfully._

The dict or config file options are just that - optional and used only if an override is needed. Such overrides will reside in a separate tree and never be part of this tree or OpenStack KC.

2. The changes have nothing to do with the CLI and only affect the API with the constraint that the default "out of the box" core keystone behavior is not altered and no other changes are required of existing or new consumers of the API if there is no deviation from core keystone as explained in 1. above.'}, {'account_id': 901, 'date': '2013-11-20 18:47:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: (2 inline comments)

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-11 17:02:50.000000000', 'message': 'Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using the
"--pre" option which is the default in tox.  "--pre" means "Include
pre-release and development versions."  By default, pip will only
install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using the
"--pre" option which is the default in tox.  "--pre" means "Include
pre-release and development versions."  By default, pip will only
install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>

commit_message:
Use setup.py develop for tox install

tox 1.6 was released, so, we can use new develop mode that'll speed up
project installation. Additionally it ensures that installation performs
without --pre to avoid alpha/beta versions.

Change-Id: Ibb54de56af965a4c9ac9f04f88d4a65a9e8862ec

commit_message:
Add -U flag to pip install command

The -U flag makes tox able to upgrade all packages to the newest available
version.

Change-Id: I608528f462d85b8838209b75fce0e9df73e4e19b

commit_message:

commit_message:
add router binding into firewall

In this patch, I removed the limit that one
tenant just has only one firewall.

I allow user to bind a router when creating or
update a firewall. On agent side, the agent will
just apply the hosted routers' related firewalls.

Implements: blueprint router-firewall-binding
Change-Id: I3a6446c2e8dcfe1998f2520185db6bf482100309

I agree with Henry's comments, and I'd like Sukhdev to answer them before this gets merged."}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2013-12-09 03:53:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I'm sorry, and it may just be because of the weekend, but I don't understand how do you install jsonrpclib when none of the package managers have a package with that name?"}, {'account_id': 6524, 'date': '2013-12-09 05:11:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I am learning as I go, so please shoot down any wrongs that I write here.

As Dean pointed out, install_package is for things managed by apt (Ubuntu), yum (Redhat), etc. And jsonrpclib is not in any of those package distributions, so this is not the right fix for the bug.

Now, jsonrpclib is in pypi so it could be installed by pip_install, but pip_install is not meant for installing packages in neutron's requirements.txt. That should be done by neutron's installer.

And when neutron is installed, jsonrpclib does get installed. So the bug is something to do with the ML2 plugin somehow not seeing/loading jsonrpclib. The ML2 plugin only needs jsonrpclib if the Arista mechanism driver for ML2 is loaded.

There is a note in the bug that specifying 'name_order=True' to the ML2 type driver extension manager initializatioln fixes the issue, but I have not the foggiest clue why/how the type driver initialization would fix this, since it is Arista's mechanism driver that uses jsonrpclib."}, {'account_id': 6558, 'date': '2013-12-11 19:43:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hi Henry, 

Thanks for your comments, suggestions and insight. 

I wanted to provide some background and some info on some poking around that I have been doing. 
First the background: 
Since Arista is the first one to use jsonrpclib, we had bundled it with Arista driver (this is back in April/May time frame - during Grizzly release cycle). Folks on review board suggested that since this is a generic python library and would eventually be used by many others as OpenStack community grows, this should be made as a generic OpenStack requirement. Hence, it made it into the openstack/requirements.txt in Grizzly release. 

Now, back to the issue at hand. I have been using both pip install  as well apt-get install and it has been working fine. As to the best way to solve it - considering that this is a python library, I am tempted to change the code to pip install (instead of instal_package), but, am concerned it may still have some issue. I could tie it to the Arista driver, but, this will defeat the purpose and the argument made in the past. Who ever needs to use it in the future, will have to replicate the code. 

So, I am turning back to the experts on this forum to seek suggestions. 

-Sukhdev'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2013-12-13 20:15:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

According to the comments, jsonrpclib is only required when q-svc is enabled.  If so, adding 'files/*/q-svc' files containing 'jsonrpclib' will install the module from pypi only when q-svc is enabled.  No script changes are necessary."}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-12-21 06:03:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Abandoned

code review expired after 1 week of no activity after a negative review, it can be restored using the `Restore Change` button under the Patch Set on the web interface'}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-12-21 06:03:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
ML2 can't seem to load type drivers

fixes bug: 1221781

When ML2 plugin is initialized using Devstack, jsonrpclib is not
installed. This prevents some type drivers from starting up.

A fix is introduced such that when ML2 plugin is configured using
devstack, jsonroplib is installed. This package needs to be installed
only on the server node. Hence the package is installed in routine
neutron_plugin_configure_service().
Initially, it is used by Arista mechanism driver.
In future, it may be used by other drivers as well.

Change-Id: Iafceeaed872192c2c4d2101d05ad68183b60ee49

[{'created': '2013-10-22 06:37:10.000000000', 'message': 'VlanManager creates superfluous quota reservations

The VlanManager does not enforce quotas on fixed IPs because it
allocates an entire network to a project. However the process
of deallocating an IP address still creates an entry in the
reservations table.

The VlanManager now loads the NoopQuotaDriver and no longer
writes superflously to the database.

Change-Id: Idf95085a5c1f4e71f3f0fc92618607073602eed3
Fixes: Bug #1204714
(cherry picked from commit 0224bca0cf0a159b096633c776d14279e33a5730)
'}]
commit_message:
VlanManager creates superfluous quota reservations

The VlanManager does not enforce quotas on fixed IPs because it
allocates an entire network to a project. However the process
of deallocating an IP address still creates an entry in the
reservations table.

The VlanManager now loads the NoopQuotaDriver and no longer
writes superflously to the database.

Change-Id: Idf95085a5c1f4e71f3f0fc92618607073602eed3
Fixes: Bug #1204714
(cherry picked from commit 0224bca0cf0a159b096633c776d14279e33a5730)

commit_message:
Adds hypervisor support for Nova V3 API

Adds support and tests for the os-hypervisors extension
for the Nova V3 API.

Note that compared to the V2 API it separates the search
function into search by hypervisor name and a new list
servers by hypervisor as this better first the changes
in the V3 API. The listing of servers by hypervisor command
is preserved, though reworked to use the new interfaces.

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

Change-Id: I472f9acad895dcf842e93d2de27530652f73867e

Adds services support for Nova V3 API

Adds support and tests for the os-services extension
for the Nova V3 API

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

commit_message:
Adds second part of quotas support for Nova V3 API

Adds support and tests for the os-quota-class-sets
extension for the Nova V3 API. Note that compared to
the V2 version this removes the ability to set quotas
which are not relevant to the V3 API (eg injected file
quotas are not relevant because the os-personalities
extension has been removed).

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

Change-Id: I3e7f36407f2f59737ecbce2c8ce014cef623ecdc

commit_message:
Ensure we are not exhausting the sqlalchemy pool

Because of eventlet, notification messages can be consumed more quickly
that than they are wroted to the database, this have to effect to exhaust
the sqlalchemy connection pool and raise:

TimeoutError: QueuePool limit of size 5 overflow 10 reached, connection
timed out, timeout 30

The patch creates a eventlet pool to ensure that the pool never exhausts
and prints a warning message in the log to inform that perhaps the pool
size need to be increased.

Fixes bug #1243251

Change-Id: I5ccdc141c441db32fab361783a31a96015516878

[{'created': '2013-10-02 23:16:17.000000000', 'message': "Check Neutron port quota during validate_networks in API

Unless ports are passed into Nova it will create ports on the
requested networks as part of the network allocation in
the compute manager.  However if the user exceeds there
port quota the instance will end up in an Error state, having
first been re-scheduled a number of times.

It would be much better if the quota failure was detected as
part of the network validation in the API server, so that an
error can be reported to the user and the creation failed.

A full fix would include reserving or creating the ports at
this stage, but there is no reservation mechanism in the
Neutron API, and port creation depends in some cases
on mac addresses only available on the compute manager.

Instead this change just validates the quota and adjusts the
max_count to be consistent with that quota, which doesn't
guarantee that the create will work, but does catch the
majority of cases.

Sneaks up on bug: 1172808

Change-Id: Iaaee059a6746fad68049712f94b2f8cfea6ab8dc

commit_message:
Check Neutron port quota during validate_networks in API

Unless ports are passed into Nova it will create ports on the
requested networks as part of the network allocation in
the compute manager. However if the user exceeds their
port quota the instance will end up in an Error state, having
first been re-scheduled a number of times.

It would be much better if the quota failure was detected as
part of the network validation in the API server, so that an
error can be reported to the user and the creation failed.

A full fix would include reserving or creating the ports at
this stage, but there is no reservation mechanism in the
Neutron API, and port creation depends in some cases
on mac addresses only available on the compute manager.

Instead this change just validates the quota and adjusts the
max_count to be consistent with that quota, which doesn't
guarantee that the create will work, but does catch the
majority of cases.

Refs bug: 1172808

Change-Id: Iaaee059a6746fad68049712f94b2f8cfea6ab8dc

commit_message:
List NotImplementedError as a client exception for vnc

Not all drivers implement the get_vnc_console method.  In that case,
they will raise NotImplementedError.  List this exception as a client
exception so that the rpc layer does not log a traceback when this
happens.

Change-Id: Id30fd35b36cbd222b2d8787f00fa586d1ed4f11a

subject: remove vmwareapi.vmops.get_console_output()

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-20 16:55:08.000000000', 'message': 'Stops file descriptor leaking in tests

During a test run serveral hundred WSGI servers are started, used for a
single testcase and then stopped. We were not properly killing the
greenthread in cases where we started the server, but the thread had not
started.

The problem is that a greenthead evaluates True or False depending if it
has already started running. We really just need a check to make sure
start() was called on the server. In this patch if server.greenthread is
not None that means that the server was started.

There are still other places where descriptors are leaking.

Change-Id: I06cddb97553cb2d25b7d0447634f05e2f6b163fe
'}]
commit_message:
Stops file descriptor leaking in tests

During a test run serveral hundred WSGI servers are started, used for a
single testcase and then stopped. We were not properly killing the
greenthread in cases where we started the server, but the thread had not
started.

The problem is that a greenthead evaluates True or False depending if it
has already started running. We really just need a check to make sure
start() was called on the server. In this patch if server.greenthread is
not None that means that the server was started.

There are still other places where descriptors are leaking.

Change-Id: I06cddb97553cb2d25b7d0447634f05e2f6b163fe

commit_message:
Install Guide: Clarify database node setup

Some people were not aware that they needed to install MySQL packages
on nodes. This patch rearranges the code so that we have separate
sections for controller and node and thus readers should easily
spot what needs to be done.

Change-Id: I104b949466b426e102d55bcb3c4a9cb72a0a6af9
Closes-Bug: #1250600
backport: havana

commit_message:
Document security group when using ML2 plugin

Since the ML2 plugin can concurrently support different L2 agents (or
other mechanisms) with different configurations, Neutron developpers
recommend setting firewall_driver flag in ml2 configuration.

Change-Id: I7f97128a955ded99400e25a5ef9a990260df3bf7
Closes-bug: #1262678
backport: havana
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

the sighup handling. Previously it was not possible to use
devstack's unstack.sh because the service module would always

commit_message:
sync oslo service to fix SIGHUP handling

this is a sync of the oslo service code to fix a bug found in
the sighup handling. Previously it was not possible to use
devstack's unstack.sh because the service module would always
restart under a SIGHUP, not only when the process was running as
a service. SIGHUP on a non-detached process should act like
SIGTERM. This change fixes that.

Change-Id: Ib260d82519fde5c5cb24a2c0c8a7cccd0b96b84f
Related-Bug: #1263122

commit_message:
port related volumes tests into nova v3 part1

This changeset only copies the v2 files into the appropriate v3
directories unchanged. This is being tried in order to make
reviewing of the porting easier as gerrit will display only what
is actually changed for v3 rather than entirely new files.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: I8799257fa161ebf4c8b4bc437a94c7af746b1112

commit_message:
Add extra_resources field to compute_nodes table

The compute_nodes table has informtion about allocation and
availability of a predefined set of resources (e.g. memory,
disk, vcpu). The extra_resources field will contain a json
string of arbirtrary information describing an extensible set
of resources that will be tracked by resource tracker plug-ins.

This differs from other fields containing json strings that have
been added recently, including pci_stats and metrics. In particular,
pci_stats is used for information about pci devices, whereas metrics
contains continuously monitored usage data and is updated at different
times to extra_resources and according to a different trigger.
Accordingly, it makes sense to seperate these into different fields.

This is part of: blueprint extensible-resource-tracking

Change-Id: I75e339c2a2827875078c937e57c37e85d3ad1852

commit_message:
Fix some H302 violations

Fixed some H302 violations with this patch, that is not required
to strictly follow H302, just bypass with H302 checking with "# noqa"
at the end of violations import lines.

Hi John, I've pushed a couple commits up that adds event_type table and reworks the get_events query slightly.

I was mistaken in my original interpretation of the get_events behaviour. I thought that supplying an event_filter with traits meant that the returned Events should ONLY have traits that matched the filters, but after looking further into the code, that turned out to not be the case. Instead, get_events always returns all the traits attached to an event, even if the trait does not match the event_filter.traits filter. Events are still filtered based on the supplied traits, but all traits of matched Events are returned.

Anyway, here are the two patches:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/41316
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/41391/

If you could take a look at those, that would be great. I think they cover a good part of your submission here...

Best,

-jay"}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-08-20 06:03:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11:

[{'created': '2013-08-05 17:06:01.000000000', 'message': "Add Event API

This commit adds v2/event_types, v2/events and v2/events/*/traits.
Currentyl, the event api is limitted to admin users, but is
configurable in the policy.json file. All users that are able to
access the event api can view all events in the system, it is not
restricted per project id. In this commit, only the first trait
filter is looked at. Operators other than 'eq' have not been
implemented either.

implements bp specify-event-api

Change-Id: I0ccd4ef81cac5f8f57a450dc980ea85ff8fe89ec

commit_message:
Add Event API

This commit adds v2/event_types, v2/events and
v2/events/*/traits. Currently, the event api is
limited to admin users, but is configurable in
the policy.json file. All users that are able to
access the event api can view all events in the
system, it is not restricted per project id.
Operators other than 'eq' have not yet been
implemented.

This change re-names the parameters in the
event_filter to class so they are more
end-user friendly.

implements bp specify-event-api

Change-Id: I0ccd4ef81cac5f8f57a450dc980ea85ff8fe89ec

commit_message:
Re-write comment for ADMIN_TOKEN

It seems that there is a misconception around the ADMIN_TOKEN in
keystone. Currently the comment read that it is a "shared secret"
and can be used between openstack services.

However this token has no user associated with it, and no
authorization. It's a method to bootstrap into keystone, that's
all.

Closes-Bug: 1261622
Co-Authored-By: Dolph Mathews <dolph.mathews@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I6c913a8079bb84b56ac69249e7d25bc94cf32dd0

commit_message:
Move Assignment Controllers and Routers to be First Class

The assignment and identity controllers and routers have been intermixed
since they were the same subsystem. The split of Identity and Assignment
at the manager level has completed.

This change continues the process and makes the Assignment controllers
and router definitions part of the assignment subsystem instead of part
of Identity. In part, this is also a continuation of clarifying where domain
lookups (for per-domain-identity backend logic) occurs.

Identity maintains a simple subclass-proxy of each Controller that was
moved to maintain compatibility for clean deprecation until Icehouse
has been released and development opens up for J.

bp: assignment-controller-first-class
bp: deprecated-as-of-icehouse
related-bug: #1218094
Change-Id: If9a206692704005284e619679e1b6fe8b08bf8c9

subject: Remove Identity and Assignment controller interdependancies

The DomainV3 controller explicitly instantiated the UserV3, GroupV3
and ProjectV3 controllers to call some delete methods. This makes it
very difficult to isolate the controllers from each other and
incorrectly implemented some logic that should exist in the
credential_api.

The code for deleting credentials by project and by user is now
implemented on the credential_api. This allows the controllers
to directly ask the credential_api to perform the deletes (and
in the case of the SQL backend, perform a more efficient delete
process).

The DomainV3 controller properly uses the identity_api to cleanup
users and groups when deletion occurs. Likewise, DomainV3 controller
now properly calls the assignment_api to perform project deletions.

These changes have been done to aid in clarifying explicit uses of
the per-domain-identity backend logic.

commit_message:
Remove Identity and Assignment controller interdependancies

The DomainV3 controller explicitly instantiated the UserV3, GroupV3
and ProjectV3 controllers to call some delete methods. This makes it
very difficult to isolate the controllers from each other and
incorrectly implemented some logic that should exist in the
credential_api.

The code for deleting credentials by project and by user is now
implemented on the credential_api. This allows the controllers
to directly ask the credential_api to perform the deletes (and
in the case of the SQL backend, perform a more efficient delete
process).

The DomainV3 controller properly uses the identity_api to cleanup
users and groups when deletion occurs. Likewise, DomainV3 controller
now properly calls the assignment_api to perform project deletions.

These changes have been done to aid in clarifying explicit uses of
the per-domain-identity backend logic.

bp: assignment-controller-first-class
related-bug: #1218094
Change-Id: Ie8ed8bce556fe2f41cc7db61f04eefaf14f836f1

[{'created': '2013-12-17 19:27:39.000000000', 'message': "Add 'next' link when GET maximum number of items

When GET'ing items from a collection with no limit parameter specified
in the request, the API gets the limit value from the configuration file
(default is max_limit=1000). However, in the case where there are more
than max_limit items, the API was not returning a 'next' link to retrieve
the next subset of items.

It turns out that the max_limit value wasn't being passed to the
*Collection.convert_with_links method. This fixes that issue by moving

Change-Id: I81e734a951e4025f64a5d572656d627e4126b353
Closes-Bug: #1250804

commit_message:
Add 'next' link when GET maximum number of items

When GET'ing items from a collection with no limit parameter specified
in the request, the API gets the limit value from the configuration file
(default is max_limit=1000). However, in the case where there are more
than max_limit items, the API was not returning a 'next' link to retrieve
the next subset of items.

It turns out that the max_limit value wasn't being passed to the
*Collection.convert_with_links method. This fixes that issue by moving
the collection call into the same method that determines the limit value.

Change-Id: I81e734a951e4025f64a5d572656d627e4126b353
Closes-Bug: #1250804

commit_message:
fix: properly pass the sleep parameter

There is no need to call super here. This patch avoid the following
error:

Validate method failed for class sleep:

  implicit argument passing of super from method defined by
  define_method() is not supported. Specify all arguments explicitly.

Closes-Bug: #1260732

Change-Id: Ic4d0a94be5104eb468d10f3d383eaa4d1fbc31d1

commit_message:
Create swift operator keystone roles

Defining operator_roles in swift-proxy.conf requires
that these roles exist in keystone.

Because Keystone API access is not available on Swift
proxy hosts in most cases, operator_roles keystone
roles have been added to swift::keystone::auth class.

Added basic docs for swift::keystone::auth

Change-Id: Ib8454f8ae1316d2589ff228ec1424c6cff69c6b5
Closes-Bug: #1261662

commit_message:
horizon replaced nodejs by a python alternative

since commit a0739c9423a4c559b45af96fa4cdb30539dcdbd7 and the Havana
release, horizon uses a pure Python alternative to nodejs.

Horizon changed the way to use the compress utility, the option
offline_compress is no longer available.
Thanks to Maxime Vidori for the information.

Change-Id: Ie290701b00c97352838e13182b940a6de46a591f

commit_message:
Add docstring for exception handlers of session

In code review, some projects are using try/except within the
context managed by session. That's wrong, add the note in
docstring, hope others put try/except in right place.

Database Errors like IntegrityError will be raised in session's
__exit__ handler, and any try/except within the context managed
by session will not be triggered. And catching other non-database
errors in the session will not trigger the ROLLBACK, so exception
handlers should always be outside the session, except developer
want to commit parts of stuff on purpose.

Closes-Bug: #1262065

Change-Id: I23223fbe9b6d9fa8e92e59894fb3b1fa195be159

Why you remove code, which assigns trunks list to an interface?
Without trunks list on interface (e.g. eth1) only ports, incomings to "interface bridge" (e.g. br-eth1) directly, will added automatically (by ovs vlan splinters technology).

In Our network topology we have 2nd level bridges, that connected to a interface bridges by virtual patchcords. Tags, from ports of 2nd level bridges, will not automatically added by vlan splinters. We have interfaces with specific behavior (e.g. br-prv), that not contains any ports, but pass tagget 802.1q traffic. This traffic also will not processed by vlan splinters without specify trunks list on incoming interface.'}, {'account_id': 8797, 'date': '2013-12-14 02:42:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Address splinters performance by having two settings instead of one.

vlan_spliters will not create a hard trunk list, it will only enable
 the vlan splinters work around in OVS

vlan_splinters_trunks will enable OVS flag and will create hard trunk
 list. This may be necessary in some deployments.

This also needs https://review.openstack.org/62513 for the UI option
 to support setting.

Closes-Bug: #1257604

Change-Id: Id034a98e10eee8e8ba9af2de0bd36aa199e2db02

[{'created': '2013-12-20 20:11:31.000000000', 'message': 'Add doc on glance property protection

In Havana, glance added a new feature: protection over

explaining it to the config reference.

commit_message:
Added steps to upgrade and reboot system after adding OpenStack repos

After adding the OpenStack repos, several distributions need to
upgrade additional packages and sometimes this includes the kernel.
Rebooting also guarantees that all changes will take effect.  I
attempted to cover all distributions with this patch.

Change-Id: I97fbf8f9ce3ff8a403ccbd90f1b0c38d915d9369
Closes-Bug: #1258279
(cherry picked from commit a31e3b9400f40d8c225f109c7c0c718b872c129b)

commit_message:
Fixed 'openstack-config' commands in controller nova.conf

Corrected section from 'DEFAULT' to 'keystone_authtoken' for the
following keys: auth_host, admin_user, admin_tenant_name,
admin_password

Added commands for the following keys: auth_protocol, auth_port

Closes-Bug: #1261927
(cherry picked from commit 5ddc758384b7d4d4f64279d097f96b4e3cfff334)

commit_message:
moving to global lazy loaded config

one of the problems we've got with tempest is the fact that config
loading is tied into the class hierarchy. However there is no
reason why it should be. If we instead create a config proxy
object we can lazy load the actual config when we are executing,
and not do it at import time.

This could use future iteration, but it does a huge job in
removing config from the object inheritance tree which massively
simplifies our ability to use config variables throughout the code.

Change-Id: I9b1bbfe231c85c01938bd68be4e5974bd24130d6

commit_message:
Allow resizes and migrates during live upgrade

This patch completes the changes needed to havana's compute rpc api to
allow live upgrades to icehouse.  Specifically, these changes are needed
to allow resizes and migrates to work.  Before havana compute nodes get
put in a mixed environment with icehouse compute nodes, they need to be
speaking version 3.0 messages.

Change-Id: If09bd38c9d8c3beb5b95107c497699dec47aa3ef
Closes-bug: #1258253

commit_message:
Allow compute manager to accept 3.0 messages

We are currently trying to support live upgrades from havana to
icehouse.  This change is required to make that happen.  In a live
upgrade situation, you have icehouse nova infrastructure, with a mix of
havana and icehouse compute nodes as you roll through and upgrade them.
While in this situation, the havana compute nodes must be able to accept
3.0 messages.

Accepting 3.0 messages is trivial to do and extremely low risk.  It does
not change the behavior of a havana-only deployment at all.  The only
additions is some pass-through code to the current compute manager.
This code will only get hit during a live upgrade situation.

Note that there is one other change needed to complete this.  With only
this patch, live upgrades are supported, but any operations that require
compute nodes to talk to each other will not work.  This includes
resizes and migrates.  That would be unfortunate, since live migrations
are something that people *definitely* want to be able to do during an
upgrade procedure.

The additional changes needed to allow resizes and migrates during live
upgrades are included in another patch.

Partial-bug: #1258253
Change-Id: Ia801609b6b3fe88e0d0b16f4c0d37bf25dbfa842

commit_message:
Fix interprocess locks when running unit-tests

When running unit-tests concurrently using testr, we might
need to use interprocess file locks (e.g. for running various
tests using the same DB in MySQL/PostgreSQL).

At the same time file locks are only usable when they are placed
to one dir, and we have a test fixture that overrides the lock_path
config value for each test case with a new temporary directory.

The solution is to create the one temprorary directory for locks
to be used by all tests before running tests and then remove it
after running tests. The corresponding helper has been already
put to openstack.common.lockutils module, we just need to reuse
it properly, i.e. change the way unit tests are run in tox.ini.

Closes-Bug: #1261728

Change-Id: I76f95a9f7fdd31c15e6cf4fd6316c7569284f780

commit_message:
Use six.seraise() instead of `raise exc, val, tb`

Python 3 doesent support odl `raise exception, value, traceback` syntax,
so we should use six.reraise() to make code compatible with python 3.

Related to blueprint make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: If66983d94667a3d3b0e809d4c0767b0829394f67

commit_message:
Remove string.lowercase usage

Python 3 has no `lowercase` in string module, so we should use
`ascii_lowercase` instead of it.

Related to blueprint make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: I8407db72fc37c14d189698c1d51b1d9b45769760

commit_message:
fileutils: do not hardcode /tmp usage

It's actually not always /tmp on all operating systems, especially if
the TMPDIR environment variable is set.

Change-Id: I9bc67769a39535dfeafe8c60aa63792e21ac9703

commit_message:
log all test messages not just oslo ones

This is a bit frustrating at the moment as you don't project specific
error messages when a test fails (it only shows the oslo logging messages).

By removing the 'openstack.common', we get all logs.

Change-Id: I1a018038be0ac82ead27814a357b50d0514087fb

commit_message:
Rename create_test_server to create_server

Because BaseComputeTest.create_test_server has the pattern "test"
in the name, the nose test runner tries to run it as a test. As
a result, the test gets run once for every ttime a test that
inherits from BaseComputeTest or its subclasses is run.

Change-Id: I102406d8a2a02dfc6f29da40aec86e692f365ad7
Closes-Bug: #1263206

commit_message:
Merge openstack/common/service.py for bug 1263122

disable SIGHUP restart behavior in foreground

SIGHUP should only be a restart action for a daemonized processs,
when used on a console process SIGHUP should == SIGTERM. Add
detection for whether this service is actually daemonized.

Change-Id: I2a73d3872a302fcfac1a6ee844a44faa9569b3dd
Fixes-Bug: 1263122

Okay, the old way of creating a table for testing, and you're proposed new way (using migrations) are going to cause us some hassle here.

The migrations create the columns in a different order than the SQLAs `Session.create_all()`.

You've added this as field #2, while the migration will append this column to the end, making it #13.

We'll need to update our InsertFromSelect to accept a list of column names to insert into.. I'll have a look at this now."}, {'account_id': 741, 'date': '2013-12-20 13:26:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I've updated InsertFromSelect, and the PowerDNS backend here[1] for this issue.. That should resolve this issue, at least for the PowerDNS backend's use of InsertFromSelect.


[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/63400"}, {'account_id': 8864, 'date': '2013-12-20 20:10:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Abandoned

See Kiall's comment above."}]

commit_message:
Fix PowerDNS not using recordset_id

When updating domains on server create, the PowerDNS backend didn't use
the designate_recordset_id field, despite it being present in the
schema.

Change-Id: Icef2612058b3af3bd0b9136a0fffddb336fb0e03
Closes-Bug: 1262837

commit_message:
Comment related to device name in attach volumes

Comment in "Attach Volumes to instances" ("Manage volumes" section), in
order to inform that device name may not match the one proposed by the user.
This limitation is related to hypervisor settings.
The documentation of this issue was recommended by John Griffith in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60257/

backport: havana
Related-Bug: #1217874

Change-Id: Ifa65ec6eecca23e85786b0fd79ae3b8ef8ebd537

Allow running of proxy and storage on the same node.

This adds conditionals to support a installation
in which a user desires to run both swift proxy and
storage on the same node.

Change-Id: I0cc827525968a9d1dc836c553a39f0ac13c4667e
(cherry picked from commit af129f0a93009293dba610ee487a41fb15027336)

commit_message:
Calculate partition power for swift

Calculage partition power according to
https://answers.launchpad.net/swift/+question/211929

power = int(log2(devnumber*100)) + resize_factor

resize_factor can be set in $::fuel_settings['swift'] hash.
default value: 2 (2048 partitions in standard setup)

Change-Id: Icbc518b05f8170b8656b6aad701bf3cece89f74f
Related-bug: #1261659

commit_message:
Adding additional tests for novaclient ssh

There's a few gaps in the testing regime for do_ssh, specifically
around IPv6, specifying identity files, and additional args. This
patch attempts to address these.

Change-Id: I590fd7ffe1e3470c8507d7f7fb2abcfdb6162561

(1 inline comment)

I was +1 on this long ago and then Alessandro found some problems, then lost track of it. Looking at it again, Alessandro's comments were addressed.

I do agree with Alessandro's comment back on 11/13 that this should really be two patches, one for the class name constants refactoring and one for the bug fix. However, I actually think that lumping those into a single patch slows down the review process. Breaking changes down into self-contained patches in a series is easier and faster to review in my opinion, and also allows us to revert changes if they cause problems later on.

Given how long this has been around though and the fact that if it does break, it's only going to break the non-standard path, i.e. hyper-v vs libvirt (used in the gate), I'll be less strict on requiring it being split into multiple patches.  It's something to remember for next time though."}, {'account_id': 8622, 'date': '2013-12-20 16:11:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: (1 inline comment)

commit_message:
Fixes get_vm_storage_paths issue for Hyper-V V2 API

Add get_vm_storage_paths function to vmutilsv2.py

get_vm_storage_paths implementation on Hyper-V V2 API changed
compared to previous V1 API. In previous V1 APIs, using
Msvm_ResourceAllocationSettingData class can get storage
paths, but in V2 API, only using Msvm_StorageAllocationSettingData
class can get the storage paths.

Closes-Bug: #1248463

Change-Id: Ica73221524f162a6ffcd9dc64ee33c85fb5ad31d

Add GET method to show response with OS-EXT-VIF-NET:net_id param made a duplicate of the the original get method code, changed the sample responses to point to the new ones /api_samples/OS-EXT-VIF-NET/vifs-list-resp.json /api_samples/OS-EXT-VIF-NET/vifs-list-resp.xml Added required="true" to , rather than relying on the default value of "required" attribute. This attribute controls the appearance of (Optional) text next to params. Change the plural "interfaces" to singular "interface" since my understanding is: You can create a maximum of one virtual interface per instance per network According to this page http://docs.rackspace.com/ servers/api/v2/cn-devguide/content/api_virt_interfaces.html change all tags to

to use this markup for methods Change-Id: I68b9d4e64a91afb822168fab4df6ce551820c765 Closes-Bug: #1187293

commit_message:
LVM migration: Check if name is equal to dest_vg

The existence check of the destination volume group is wrong. It
currently checks if there's a VG with a name equal to the source's vg
name instead of checking if it's equal to the dest_vg.

Closes-bug: #1258203
(cherry picked from commit 17912f4c4fba270a15cab47bb68d9e30c34a69b0)

Change-Id: Ia5d4acb24b94c6aa832107c7eb4b6996985af97f

3. You're making this change against the quota_classes extension, which handles quota classes.  However, quotas are managed using the quotas extension, and similar code currently exists there (i.e., "value = int()"), though it's a little more complicated than that.

commit_message:
Fix parameter checking about quota update api

In quota_classes and quotas update API, parameters are checked
whether they are integer or not.
But when pass float values to these APIs, error doesn't occur.
Float values should be forbidden for the following reasons.
(1)If the value that user submitted and the value registered
   actually are different, user will be confused.
(2)Error messages of these APIs are "...must be integer...".
(3)In horizon, if a float is submitted, error message is displayed.

This patch fixes this problem.

Change-Id: I4c7df52ffff2d997da4e6267e25ec2ea4ab6f153
Closes-Bug: #1243037

commit_message:
update script should install released oslo.config

the update.sh script was still referencing a beta release off the
tarballs site, which ensured you were getting a terribly old
oslo.config. We should use a real version of oslo.config to do
updates.

Change-Id: Ia7a2c3d8e22d1d5d6afc01150ec87f3d54778606

commit_message:
Refactor engine internals

In this change we:
- introduce single graph action, that works with futures
- split methods of TaskAction into schedule/complete parts,
  with schedule* returns future;
- task executor became entity that manages Executor, instead
  of engine + graph action.

Change-Id: Ic0704534391abdd566bf2d87adabef43a9c88cfb

commit_message:
Fixed naming of expected status of a stack.

Method wait_for_stack_status in heatmanager
was waiting for "ERROR" status as reason
for test interruption but should wait
for "CREATE_FAILED" status.
Similar fix was done in cleanup.py.

Change-Id: Ib9fb5c3df3256328012d23a56bd4f78923724c6c
Closes-Bug: #1260798

commit_message:
Increase test duration displaying in expected field

Retries for transport operation was added previously
So in this patch test Duration, displaying
in Expected column on HealthCheck UI page was increased

Change-Id: I5b64eac6770ea5bce6d9eef22912cdb9afd9fb44
