revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-12 22:09:28.000000000', 'message': 'Convert numeric values in instance metadata to strings

Prior to this patch, if the following was in a template as a
"OS::Nova::Server" resource property, the user would see a "BadRequest"
error from the remote API:

metadata:
  a: 1

Fix this issue by converting the value of each metadata entry to a
string before passing the metadata to the novaclient create call.

Closes-Bug: #1260476

commit_message:
Convert numeric values in instance metadata to strings

Prior to this patch, if the following was in a template as a
"OS::Nova::Server" resource property, the user would see a "BadRequest"
error from the remote API:

metadata:
  a: 1

Fix this issue by converting the value of each metadata entry to a
string before passing the metadata to the novaclient create call.

Closes-Bug: #1260476
Change-Id: I89d60620a3b852a7fcdd2f41135b1f12fbd428d8

commit_message:
Adds images support for Nova V3 API

Adds support for basic image querying from the image server
rather than the Nova API. The Nova V3 API no longer supports
image querying directly, but in order to support convenience
functions such as specifying images by name rather than ID,
it is necessary to have some basic image query support.

image delete and image meta manipulation is no longer supported
by the client as these features can be accessed directly through
the glance client

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

Change-Id: I9050845d631e9dfc2e110327221d154b8924cd65

commit_message:
Temporary workaround for config generator

Current oslo.config.cfg.Opt doesn't support operator '=='. So use 'not
!=' instead. This is a temporary workaround before the newly released
oslo.config support the operator '=='.

Partial-Bug: 1262148

Change-Id: I19279cd211594bb107777d6b98ebe6990063ebc7

commit_message:
General updates to Compute for style and convention

Editing the top third of the compute chapter. Mostly grammar, wording,
style, convention, etc. Some minor section-level editing to improve
readability. Watch this space for more edits on these bugs.

Change-Id: If541f4a5e20251c94f6cbf416ff7c0d0e4c66892

commit_message:
Remove premature restart of Keystone service during configuration

For simplification purposes, restarting the Keystone service
should wait until after configuring all relevant directives
in keystone.conf.

Change-Id: Id26edc20236953215dd18635fbe143f4bc1bc8da
Closes-Bug: #1258651
(cherry picked from commit 26ac40e2b594a72d807815947db2832f6aa66904)

commit_message:
Corrected link to VMware KB article

Rather than replace the link wholesale, I have restored
that link and added a paragraph that better describes the
need for the procedure described in the second KB article
(Pursuant to Andreas's comment in the review).

Change-Id: Ie1cc385254f726a37f01caaaceb531ad5c31ec91
backport: havana
Closes-Bug: #1259666

'}, {'created': '2013-10-31 10:49:27.000000000', 'message': 'Database hook enabling traditional mode at MySQL

The MySQL server can operate in different SQL modes, and can apply these
modes differently for different clients, depending on the value of the
sql_mode system variable. Traditional mode Make MySQL behave like a
"traditional" SQL database system. A simple description of this mode is
"give an error instead of a warning" when inserting an incorrect value
into a column including the case when the input string is surpassing the
maximum data length of the field. Thus fixes the bug "The string greater
than the declared on column in MySQL silently truncated."

Closes-Bug: #1224898
Change-Id: I2960435c81d21f5a65ea7fa4dc5c100880cf6aef

commit_message:
Database hook enabling traditional mode at MySQL

The MySQL server can operate in different SQL modes, and can apply these
modes differently for different clients, depending on the value of the
sql_mode system variable. Traditional mode makes MySQL behave like a
"traditional" SQL database system. A simple description of this mode is
"give an error instead of a warning" when inserting an incorrect value
into a column including the case when the input string is surpassing the
maximum data length of the field.

Closes-Bug: #1224898
Change-Id: I2960435c81d21f5a65ea7fa4dc5c100880cf6aef

commit_message:
Add sleep between image detach

Image detach via qemu-nbd and disk removal
has a racy behaviour for locally placed URIs,
but not for RBD disks for example.

Closes-Bug: #1250231

Change-Id: I2a3c8f5b8db44ed831916164815c60114cf22906

commit_message:
Fix wrong vif driver by default

Some changes have been done in Nova to have generic drivers:
http://tinyurl.com/VifDriver

This patchs aims to change default driver.

Closes-bug #1259139
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
Change-Id: I38ab21b7a3ae0f5b9ec4f08f5e30d2da58381cf1

This changeset only copies the v2 files into the appropriate v3
directories unchanged. This is being tried in order to make
reviewing of the porting easier as gerrit will display only what
is actually changed for v3 rather than entirely new files.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: I55a91197dc7138e90dc59e8191c0209d9ce628c3
'}]
commit_message:
port certificates tests into nova v3 part1

This changeset only copies the v2 files into the appropriate v3
directories unchanged. This is being tried in order to make
reviewing of the porting easier as gerrit will display only what
is actually changed for v3 rather than entirely new files.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: I55a91197dc7138e90dc59e8191c0209d9ce628c3

commit_message:
Use rand_uuid and remove unused client for clean-up

This patch cleans the code of test_servers_negative.py up with the
following ways:
(1) Remove an unused client in the test file.
(2) Write some test descriptions.
(3) Import test based on http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/
(4) Use data_utils.rand_uuid() instead of str(uuid.uuid4()).
    test_servers_negative contains some tests about nonexistent
    server/flavor and nonexistent uuids are generated with str(
    uuid.uuid4()).
    Now rand_uuid() is defined in data_utils for generating their
    uuids. This patch replaces nonexistent uuids to rand_uuid().

Change-Id: I2fa423f11e7703a69720f031a8462d4eb782d76c

commit_message:
Benchmark scenarios for Rally: run task in instance

This patch allows a user to define a scenario where Nova instances are
created, then a script which outputs arbitrary JSON is run, and then the
instance is destroyed.

This allows tests/benchmarks from the instance perspective, as well as
from OS APIs.

blueprint benchmark-scenarios

Change-Id: I10c4aea91ac015457ebfae071bed8dcb870edcb6
